Place the water, salt, onion, dillweed, allspice, pepper and potatoes in a large pot and bring to a boil.  Simmer until the potatoes are almost done.  Lay the fish on top of the potatoes, cover, and simmer until the fish flakes when pierced with a fork.  With a large spoon, break the fish into pieces the same size as the potato cubes, and stir into the soup.  Add the evaporated milk and the butter, stir, and simmer for 5 minutes.  Pour into a serving bowl and garnish with fresh dill.  Serve with sour rye bread.
